A common situation where poor digital communication causes problems is when a student sends an email to a professor without proper etiquette. 
For example, writing a message like “Send me the notes ASAP” without a greeting, context, or polite tone can be seen as rude and disrespectful. 
This may lead the professor to ignore the email or develop a negative impression of the student, affecting future interactions. 
Such misunderstandings happen because tone is hard to interpret in digital communication.
This situation could have been handled better by using a clear subject line, a respectful greeting, and polite language.
For instance, the student should introduce themselves, explain their request clearly, and end with a courteous closing. 
Following basic email etiquette ensures clarity, maintains professionalism, and helps build positive relationships.
